AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FLUXO_0000123> "A data item which represents the speed of a chemical reaction turning reactive species into product species of event (i.e the number of such conversions) occuring over a time interval")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FLUXO_0000123> "flux")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FLUXO_0000123> "reaction rate")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FLUXO_0000123> "it is commonly refer to flux in MFA, even though formally it is a rate. The actual definition of metabolic flux is the amount of metabolite which is converted per time unit. It is calculated as the reaction rate times stoichiometric coefficient, often normalized to a specific quantity (e.g. cell dry weight or volume of a compartment)")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FLUXO_0000123> "metabolic flux")
